I arrived in the U.S. on the 27th of May of 2014. The soil on the plane felt dry and the world in which I was stepping was completely different than I knew it. Upon starting classes, I was placed in 9th grade this gave me 11 hours a day of free-time. I didn’t have a car nor a driver license so I would have to either depending on my friends or take the bus. I thought for myself, “is this going to be all my life is like?” First, I didn’t have nearly any clothes nor shoes to wear to school. Secondly, and worst of all my physical copy of the mathematics textbook didn’t come with my school huddles and I wasn’t about to buy another textbook even if I had the financial means to.

This new world seems never ending; its surroundings seem like they would never change but I thought to myself “I’m not going to just sit still,” I thought to myself “I want to make my surrounding place my life the best I could” and I started small. When my friends of mine were texting me to go out and bring food or drinks I would go and happily come back to the house with mountain dew, chips, and tortillas.
